Igor Ranitovic wrote:
&gt; Hello Andrew,
&gt; 
&gt; Take a look at
&gt; org.archive.crawler.datamodel.CandidateURI.getVia() method.
&gt; 
&gt; Note that the &#39;via&#39; URI itself will not have information about its own 
&gt; via URI. Therefore, I don&#39;t think that you can have a breadcrumb trail 
&gt; that is more than two links long without adding this feature yourself.
&gt; 
&gt; There are several ways to add this feature, but maybe the easiest way is 
&gt; to write a breadcrumb processor that will utilize the 
&gt; CrawlURI/CandidateURI dynamic attributes list (a.k.a aList). The aList 
&gt; is a map of key-value pairs for storing information about the URI that 
&gt; can be accessed by other processors. This breadcrumb processor can 
&gt; maintain the A_BREADCRUMB/List key-value pair where the list can hold 
&gt; all URIs visited in the path. Just keep in mind that for big crawls 
&gt; carrying over the breadcrumbs might add significant overhead to the 
&gt; overall URIs state.
&gt; 
&gt; I hope this helps.
&gt; i.
